<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">know I am straining every nerve to procure Provissions for them when they are hard at work in the Summer<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> yet they would willingly now whilst they are Idle Devour all that is to be had<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 23<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Man that brought the Meat yesterday went away, gave him 30 skins on Credit<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the Hunter to hunt hares as he does not at present find appropos to hunt orignals<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Paid S<sup>t</sup> André Two &amp; a half fathoms of Tobacco having promissed him a Carrot at Athabasca last fall for steering a Canoe here, he having had only a Middlemans Eq<sup>t</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 24<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Weighed all my present <span class="AddHand-author">Riches</span> which forms only 16 Packs viz<sup>t</sup> 9 of Beaver<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 4 of Pichous &amp; 3 of Bea<span class="AddHand-editors">[r]</span> skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Martin mad<span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span> a pair of snow shoes for the Express Men<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave him a Dram<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 25<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Melted all the Fatt which formed 100lbs of Grease<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon the Little Chiefs Two Brothers in law &amp; his youngest Son arrived &#8211; they left their Lodges this morning<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Received 27 skins of Credits, &amp; traded 10 skins all Pichues &#8211; they complain that the wolves have destroyed a great many of their Pichues &#8211; likewise traded the Meat of 2 Pichues<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 1 Small orignals Thigh &amp; 2 do Placottés &#8211; a little after they went away<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave the 28 skins Credits exclusive of the Balance of their old Debts<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 26<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon a young Man arrived &#8211; he brought 10 Hares &#8211; paid him for the same &amp; 4 skins for his share of Dry Meat that Martin found in the Cache<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 27<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Indian arrived yesterday went away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the forenoon the young Man that I employed for hunter the 24<sup>th</sup> Ins<sup>t</sup> arrived, he brought nothing.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e says that he could not find any Hares, altho he was not a moment Idle &#8211; he <span class="AddHand-author">also</span> says he missed a shot on an orignal<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[27]</span></p>

